org.orgName: The District Court of the United States, Western District of Washington, Northern Division

div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington.
In the Matter of the Application of Bartolomeo Massulo for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
Filed in the United States District Court
In the Matter of the Application of Bartolomeo Massulo for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
The petitioner and the respondent having stipulated in writing herein for the withdrawal of exhibits "A", "B" and "C" attached to respondent's return,

IT IS THEREFORE BY THE COURT HEREBY CONSIDERED AND ORDEREDD that the clerk of this Court be and he hereby is authorized and instructed to surrender and deliver said exhibits "A", "B" and "C" to the said respondent,

AND IT IS BY THE COURT FURTHER ORDERED that respondent file herein in lieu of said exhibits the original record and transcript of the proceedings before the immigration authorities and the testimony adduced in said proceedings with relation to the deportation of said applicant, and of which said record and transcript the said exhibits "A", "B" and "C" are copies.
Done in open Court this 3rd day of March, 1919.
Received above exhibits A-B and C this March. 3-1919.
Henry M. White - Commr by his attorney
Ben L. Moore Asst U.A. Atty
